      {
        "id": 1686621,
        "name": "Steve Heydemann",
        "username": "Steve_Heydemann",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/b9bd4f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2015-06-14T15:36:30.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I had the chance last week to taste the 2011 Pepe MdA, the 2012 Trebbiano, and the 2013 Cerasuolo.  The MdA, decanted, is stunning.  Classic young Pepe.  Alive in the glass, crushed red fruit, spice, smoke, well-built, lovely mouthfeel.  The Trebbiano and the Cerasuolo both show heavy brett on opening, the latter some VA that might be bothersome to those sensitive to it.  But both developed wonderfully in the glass, with the Cerasuolo showing loads of cherry but also some mineral and spice, a bit of earthiness, vibrancy and loads of potential.  Same for the Trebbiano, which was more tropical fruits and cashew, honeysuckle, and a brightness that was quite refreshing.  Both it and the Cerasuolo will be better in a few years.  I\u2019d readily buy all 3 again.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T12:50:56.813Z",
